In this speech delivered in Tempe, Arizona, President Joe Biden praises the mayor for his work and emphasizes the need to invest in America and the American people. He discusses the importance of growing the country from the middle out and the bottom up, rather than relying on trickle-down economics. Biden highlights the accomplishments of his administration, such as creating millions of jobs and securing private investments in government programs. He also talks about the challenges facing democracy, including the events of January 6th and the rise of hate rhetoric in American politics. Biden expresses his determination to lead the country and maintain America's role as a global leader. He mentions his efforts to address issues such as drug prices and negotiations with China, and emphasizes the importance of preserving democratic values. The speech concludes with Biden expressing optimism in the younger generation and their ability to bring about positive change.